body:
> @Win7GM I want to emphasize that touch events are generated for BOTH mouse cursor and virtual finger, so I prefer adding a "再“.

@yume-chan I think either way will do but if it should be emphasized I would prefer phrasing it explicitly like:
`具体来说，在鼠标，和与鼠标位置关于屏幕中心对称的位置上，_scrcpy_ 会分别生成一个“虚拟手指”用于模拟点按操作。`

@Win7GM Now the meaning of "virtual finger" differs from the original English text:

> Concretely, scrcpy generates additional touch events from a "virtual finger" at a location inverted through the center of the screen.

Although it's not unacceptable.

@rom1v I did the old translation, but when I read it again now, some word choices are pretty bad.

@epiciskandar's initial change is good, but I want to discuss and improve the whole section taking this opportunity.

@Win7GM and I mostly agreed on the above version, the problem now is @epiciskandar mixed the second and third paragraphs up.

So after changing that or maybe several more discussions after this PR will be good to go.
